NEW YORK & NEW JERSEY STEAMBOAT COMPANY, Appellee, v. THE Ferryboat PHILADELPHIA, Her Engines, Etc., PENNSYLVANIA RAILROAD CO., Appellant. No. 65. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Dec. 4, 1933. Burlingham, Veeder, Eearey, Clark & Hupper, of New York City (Stanley R. Wright, and Chauneey I. Clark, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Purdy & Purdy, of New York City (John E. Purdy and William F. Purdy, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before L. HAND, SWAN, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed without opinion.
